      {
        "purpose": "modern_jp_reading",
        "value": "貮口合 平均（にこうごうへいきん）七十二万四千七百三十九石余 — 五ヶ年平均"
      },
      {
        "purpose": "english_translation",
        "value": "Two-mouth combined, 5-year average = 724,739.3152 koku. Saga's distinctive phrasing for what is essentially godaka: the combined high of formal + new-field, averaged over five years. EXACT MATCH with the Tōkei Shūshi figure (724,739). The 貮口合 (ni-kō-gō) phrasing reflects the domain's split-territory administrative pattern."
      },
      {
